description:
&lt;p&gt;The fetal medicine unit (FMU) at St Thomas is a tertiary referral centre. The FMU runs a first trimester screening service through a One Stop Clinic for Assessment of Risk (OSCAR) model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sonographers undertake first and second trimester screening and specialised anomaly and growth scans for high risk pregnancies which run alongside consultant led clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department also supports scanning in the Emergency Pregnancy and Acute Gynaecology Unit (EPAGU), Maternity Assessment Unit (MAU) and the Assisted Conception Unit (ACU).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for two sonographers to join our team. We have a full time position (37.5 hours per week) and a part time position available (30 hours per week).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- work as an independent sonographer by performing ultrasound scans to a high standard, formulate a report and communicate the results to women&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- work in partnership with the fetal medicine Consultants and specialist fetal medicine and screening midwives&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- the post holder will be expected to participate with multi-disciplinary team meetings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- to develop and improve professional expertise via continuous professional development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact the FMU Matron Debbie Bridgewater and or Alison Smith the Tutor Sonographer for more information on this post or if you wish to have an informal visit. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; debbie.bridgewater@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt; alison1smith@gstt.nsh.uk&lt;/p&gt;
